# Static pages must be matched BEFORE the SPA catch-all, otherwise
# these URLs would get rewritten to index.html and render the React
# app shell. They're linked from external app-verification consoles
# (Meta, Google OAuth, LinkedIn, X) and need to be reachable without
# logging in.
#
# /policy is an alias for /privacy because that's the path registered
# in the Google OAuth consent screen — verification fails when
# /policy returns the same HTML as the home page (the SPA shell).
/privacy         /privacy.html         200
/policy          /privacy.html         200
/data-deletion   /data-deletion.html   200

# Everything else falls through to the SPA shell.
/*   /index.html   200
